cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image captioning and saliency prediction models. It could also belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-category as it involves generating captions using recurrent neural networks. The paper also involves training and optimizing neural networks, which could place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the use of saliency information to improve image captioning could be considered as an application of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of large-scale datasets for experiments could place this paper in the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
